  "texts": [
    "Moreover, changing the Higgs bundle by a gauge transformation also does not change the isometry type of the soliton.Theorem C has the following drawback for producing examples of solitons from Ansatz 3.1: if G is the reductive group associated to a nilsoliton (N, h), then we must apply Theorem C to Higgs bundles with G 0 -Higgs bundles since the non-abelian Hodge correspondence (cf.",
    "Theorem 4.8) is currently only known for connected groups.",
    "Hence, we only produce solitons (M, g) such that ρ(π 1 (B)) ≤ G 0, where ρ is the twisting homomorphism of π: M → B.",
    "However, this is not a major drawback since we do produce everything up to taking a finite cover.",
    "Indeed, the cover B → B such that π 1 ( B) = ker ρ, where ρ is the composition of ρ with the projection G → G/G 0, is finite and the twisting homomorphism of the pullback of M to B maps into G 0."
